Define: I should see the hash syntax has been replaced with the properties from the dog model
        AssertValue id name text = "Alfie"
        AssertValue id breed text = "Collie"
        AssertValue id colour text = "Brown"
        AssertValue id height text = "16 inches"
        
Define: If I then update the name of the dog in the model
        click the "Update Dogs Name" button

Define: I should see that the dogs name has changed in the bound node
        AssertValue id name text = "Donald"

Define: The <INPUT_ID> input should contain "<COLOUR>", the original colour of the dog
        FindById <INPUT_ID>
        AssertCurrentInput value="<COLOUR>"

        
Define: If I type "<COLOUR>" into the <INPUT_ID> input
        ClearAndSendKeys "<COLOUR>" to id <INPUT_ID>

Define: Then tab off of the element
        SendKey Key.TAB

Define: The <ID> in the table should be update to <COLOUR>
        AssertValue id <ID> text = "<COLOUR>"
        
Define: I should see the dogs collar is <COLOUR>
        AssertValue id collarColour text = "<COLOUR>"

Define: And if I change the collar to blue
        click the "Set collar to blue" button

Define: And if I remove the collar
        click the "Remove collar" button

Define: Then put a pink one on
        click the "Add pink collar" button

Define: I should see the colour of the collar is not shown
        AssertValue id collarColour text = ""
        
Define: I should see the <ATTRIBUTE> of the <ID> element is <COLOUR>
        FindById <ID>
        AssertCurrentElement attribute="<ATTRIBUTE>" value="<COLOUR>" 